    "docHtml": "<p>A six-foot shaft topped with an axe-blade, a hammer, and a spike or hook, giving the wielder three ways to strike or bind. The poleaxe excels against armored men-at-arms in melee or mounted combat, the hammer for crushing plate, the spike for between-joint thrusts. A weapon of knights unmounted and professional soldiers, requiring long training and both hands.</p>\n",
